{
  "stem": "1753.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 74.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because of anti-Semitism, the non-Jews wouldn't subscribe to a Jewish engineer's in this town and the work that he was performing.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So-- and I worked there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I installed and I learned the trade.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the next basic event-- main event, in my view, as I remember-- that took place was when I received a postal card from my mother [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] about-- that would have been maybe the first or second day of November of 1938.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And she writes in that card that she, my brother, my sister-- they were deported from Germany because of their stateless or Polish citizenship.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Even though we children were born in Germany there, unlike than other-- than in other countries-- the US, for example-- you are a citizen of the country what your father is a citizen of.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So my father-- he was born in Poland.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He came to Germany as a little child.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "His parents nor he ever took out citizenship for Germany.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Among that group of Jews that were deported to Germany was a family by the name of Grynszpan, and a mother, a father, and I believe another couple of children, who at that time had a son who was a student-- whose son was a student in Paris.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The reason I mention this-- because later on, you will see what the connection was between it and the Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So anyway, I received that postal card.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And obviously she had to-- my mother tells me they got kicked out and I should go back to our village and see what I could salvage and send back to them to Poland.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They didn't pick me up because I was a minor.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
